<FIRST>r i AM-TyphoonRoger     08-27 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Typhoon Roger,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Dead, Two Missing as Tropical Storm Hits Western Japan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm with 55 mph winds and heavy rains caused
landslides and flooding Sunday that left two people dead and three
missing, police said.
   Seven people were reported injured by objects thrown by the winds.
   The storm, earlier designated Typhoon Roger, had been downgraded
to a tropical storm by the time it hit western Japan, forecasters
said.
   The heavy rains flooded 550 houses, caused about 70 landslides
and damaged or destroyed roads in 40 places, a police official said.
   The storm hit Cape Muroto on Sunday morning and had moved north
to Fukui in central Japan by early evening, forecasters said.
   The police official said a 61-year-old man was buried by a
landslide in Ome on the outskirts of Tokyo, and an 8-year-old girl
drowned after falling into a swollen river in Saitama state
northwest of Tokyo.
   The official said three men were missing. Two of them fell into
flooded rivers, one while repairing a bridge.
</TEXT>
