<HEAD>Commander Fired after Defeats; Troops Sent for Retraining</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A battalion commander has been fired
and his troops ordered to undergo retraining for suffering a defeat
this month at the hands of Communist rebels, the military announced.
   Maj. Gen. Ramon Montano said Saturday he relieved Col. Nestor
Adaza, commander of the 58th Infantry Battalion, after his troops
wandered into a rebel ambush Aug. 20 on Mindanao island.
   Eleven soldiers were killed, 12 were wounded and one was reported
missing after the clash, he said. Troops also lost firearms and
communications equipment to the rebels.
