the need to show the government's ``strong commitment'' against
crime.
   ``We have to make a bold move to give a signal to the gun
smugglers that the government will not tolerate their illegal
activities,'' the Sunday Times quoted Mrs. Aquino as saying.
   Military officials estimate there are 180,000 unlicensed firearms
nationwide, including those in rebel hands.
