<FIRST>r a AM-PrisonFight 1stLd-Writethru a0737 08-27 0229</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Prison Fight, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0737,0230</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prison Fight Injures More Than 30</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS lead, INSERTS 1 graf after 4th, `Six inmates...,' to UPDATE
with more injuries.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORAVIA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 30 inmates were injured Sunday
night when a fight broke out at an upstate medium-security prison,
authorities said.
   About 200 inmates were in the prison yard near the outdoor
weight-lifting equipment when the fight erupted at about 7:45 p.m.
at the Cayuga Correctional Facility, according to state corrections
spokesman James Flateau.
   Flateau said prison guards broke up the fight and returned the
inmates to their dormitories by 8:35 p.m.
   Six inmates were taken to hospitals and 12 others were being
treated for injuries at the prison infirmary, Flateau said. Most of
the injuries involved cuts and bruises and none was serious, he
said. No guards were hurt.
   Fourteen other inmates were later sent to the prison infirmary
after being checked by guards, Flateau said.
   Flateau said Cayuga, which opened in 1988, currently holds 972
inmates, which is near its capacity. Among them are 175 being housed
in the prison gymnasium as part of a state plan to ease overcrowding
in local jails.
   ``At this point we don't know which inmates were involved'' in
the fight or what caused it, Flateau said.
   Cayuga is in central New York about 45 miles southwest of
Syracuse.
</TEXT>
